beer_description: Triple IPA brewed with Cashmere and Mosaic hops.
Our base sour golden ale with guava and tangerine.
Berliner Weisse Style Ale with Gewurtztraminer grapes.

Inflections of hearth-risen country bread interwoven with notes of nutmeg, clove, banana skin, and Asian pear create quite the beguiling beverage. Our New World love of the Old World classics allowed us to marry North Carolina wheat malt with time-honored German brewing techniques and ingredients. Simply delicious.
Collab with Half Barrel Beer Project
Imperial stout brewed with maple syrup, with pecans and natural flavors added.

Made with good old-fashioned hop-bursting techniques and irresponsible dry-hopping technology, Bound by Time is an offering to those looking for something brimming with hop character and as unadulterated as a butterfly’s wing.
Blonde Ale w/ Strawberry & Vanilla.
Brewed with peanut butter, grape juice, and milk sugar for that sandwich in a glass experience. 5-5.5%

Our Ultra-Deluxe Premium Blonde Ale, crafted with the finest barley, hand-selected hops, and superlative water, is built for the fridge and destined for your hand. Refreshment and refinement never tasted so premium.
Hazy, juicy, NEIPA. Hopped with Azacca, El Dorado, and Huell Melon.
Zesty and tropical pale ale brewed with a touch of malted rye and Citra hops.
Juicy IPA hopped with Citra, Azacca, and El Dorado.
Hazy NE-style double IPA dry hopped with over 5 lbs/bbl of Azacca, El Dorado, and Ci Show More
Our flagship American IPA. Hopped with Amarillo, Centennial, Cascade, and Simcoe.
Southeast-Asian inspired witbier lightly spiced with ginger and lemongrass.
Our interpretation of the traditional German-style sour wheat beer, brewed with coriander and grey sea salt. Sour, salty, delicious.
Sour ale with lemon, milk sugar, cinnamon, graham crackers, and Madagascar vanilla. When life gives you lemons, make PIE.
Get your freaky tiki on with this tropical spiced pineapple, passionfruit, and guava smoothie sour. IT IS TIME TO TIKI.
Milkshake IPA with pineapple, coconut, Madagascar vanilla, and milk sugar.
Milkshake IPA made with lactose, vanilla, and peanut butter.
Doppelbock lagered in horizontal tanks. Rich and malty with a touch of noble hop aroma.
Hazy IPA brewed with Mosaic and El Dorado hops.

Drinks Well with Otters is our second beer brewed in partnership with the South Carolina Aquarium. This soft and pillowy double IPA features Galaxy, Simcoe and El Dorado hops. Expect intense flavors of orange zest, ripe pineapple and peach. Proceeds benefit conservation efforts at the Aquarium.
Fruity AF
North Carolina southern select heritage malt and a splash of Hallertau hops. The result is the perfect harmony between a German Pilsner and a Charleston lager.
Our old school topic the hat to the West Coast IPA. Brewed to a dry, crisp finish with a quenching double dry hop of cascade.
Bavarian Wheat Beer
A collaboration between Revelry Brewing & Marsh Hen Mill.
New England Style IPA

A pale, refreshing and hoppy ale. Supporting malt and new world hops provide balance, drinkability and classic citrus, floral and tropical fruit characters. Go ahead… challenge the status quo… Poke The Bear!

Golden and clear with a whipped head. Aroma of orange, spice and honey with supporting flavors. Most flavor is yeast derived and has a distinct Belgian yeast character with respect to ester/phenol profile.
American Sour Ale brewed with Pink Guava, Passion Fruit, Pineapple, and Orange Zest. Thirst quenching, tart, and punchy.

Refreshing, clean, balanced, light-bodied. Aromas subtle with floral and earthy notes. Brewed with premium organic malts from US & Germany along with combo of English and traditional American hops to the golden ale style. 50 Calories.

Our elegant premium sparkling dry cider is a reflection of soft summer hues of sunsets across the Hampton beaches. This unique hard cider is sourced from only the best New York State apples and represents a bohemian spirit that resides in everyone.
Walking a fine line of sweet malt & assertive hop character. A hop presence so enticing it truly is a work of art.
Our take on a kölsch style ale that is soft on the palate with a delicate malt flavor. Balanced with a touch of wheat and honey notes. Dry and wine like with a flowery hop finish
New England style hazy IPA hopped with Mosaic and Citra.

A crisp golden session ale, with a mildly bitter citrus finish. Perfect for the porch or the beach, this Southern brew is perfect for any occasion. Like the beautiful beaches of the Lowcountry, the Folly’s keeps you coming back again and again. Enjoy the Folly. Drink your Pride!

Generous additions of organic American hops – citrusy, grassy, and herbal – combine with organic malts to strike a perfect balance with our house ale yeast. A crisp and fresh hop-flavored IPA. Open the Green Door.

A true little bomb of flavours, it presents a perfect harmony between citrus aroma, hop freshness and bitterness. This beer guarantees a soft contact with taste buds, releasing apricot and soft caramel notes. Its exacerbated dry side makes its bouquet of flavours shine and ensures its good aromatic persistence.
